    schema:description "This project establishes a large-scale, ground-breaking interdisciplinary research program. Led by exceptional mid-career researchers from diverse backgrounds, it aims to revolutionise perinatal care for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander (Aboriginal) families. In partnership with Aboriginal community-controlled organisations, we will build infrastructure to progress towards diffusion and sustainability of community-led, culturally-responsive, evidence-based, trauma-aware, healing-informed continuity of care to enable families to foster a healthy start to life – a fundamental foundation for Closing the Gap." ;
